description:
&lt;p&gt; Heads Up Project Co-ordinator&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salary: NHS Agenda for Change Band 5&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hours per week: 37.5 hrs per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fixed Term Contract until March 2022&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Essex Partnership University NHS Foundation Trust (EPUT) is looking for an experienced and motivated professional to join our innovative, well established NHS team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This project is jointly funded by the Big Lottery Community Fund and the European Social Fund. This role will manage a dedicated team of Peer Support Workers; an employability programme supporting individuals across Essex who are long term unemployed and experiencing mental health challenges.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The central role will include the line management of Peer Support Workers, promoting the service &amp; generating referrals, management of stakeholder relationships, contractual compliance (including performance reporting, HR functions, service delivery processes), delivering on Key Performance Indicators (KPIs) and taking remedial action where necessary, service development and innovation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We operate across North East and Mid Essex. We are happy to be flexible as to where the successful candidate will be based.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information about the role please contact Raza Ahmed on 07794193654, raza@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For any support applying for this role please contact epunft.recruitment.adverts@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;EPUT are looking for motivated staff who shares our Trust values of Open, Compassionate and Empowering. In return, EPUT can offer you a range of benefits and development including;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Season Ticket Loans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS discounts for staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent Training facilities and opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Buying and Selling annual leave scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The opportunity to work bank shifts and expand knowledge and experience in other areas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Salary Sacrifice schemes including lease cars and Cycle to Work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
